                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the south base of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine in the Vṛishabhapurīśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Parāntaka I. Year 21: 927-28 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription is dated in the reign of Madiraikoṇḍa Parakēsari.</p>						
                            
                            <p>It records the endowment of sheep for a perpetual lamp for god Tiruttāṉṟōṉṟip-Pe[rumāṉaḍigaḷ] by Kū[ṟṟa]ñchēṉaṉ of Nambipuram in Pā[ṇ]ḍi-nāḍu, an agent of Brahmapallavaraiyar.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
